 <table-wrap-foot id="mpp12917-ntgp-0003">
  <title>Note</title>
  <fn id="mpp12917-note-0006">
   <p>Abbreviations for amino acids: G, glycine; E, glutamate; I, isoleucine; T, threonine; D, aspartic acid; V, valine; M, methionine.</p>
  </fn>
  <fn id="mpp12917-note-0007">
   <label>a</label>
   <p>Detailed construction maps of the infectious DNA‐A and ‐B are illustrated in Figures 
    <xref rid="mpp12917-fig-0001" ref-type="fig">1</xref>a, 
    <xref rid="mpp12917-fig-0003" ref-type="fig">3</xref>a, 
    <xref rid="mpp12917-fig-0004" ref-type="fig">4</xref>a and 
    <xref rid="mpp12917-fig-0005" ref-type="fig">5</xref>.
   </p>
  </fn>
  <fn id="mpp12917-note-0008">
   <label>b</label>
   <p>Disease incidence (%) is indicated by number of infected plants/total number of plants inoculated.</p>
  </fn>
  <fn id="mpp12917-note-0009">
   <label>c</label>
   <p>The sap was prepared from the agroinoculated 
    <italic>N. benthamiana</italic> and used as inoculum for mechanical inoculation.
   </p>
  </fn>
  <fn id="mpp12917-note-0010">
   <label>d</label>
   <p>The symbol “–“ indicates that infectivity was not determined.</p>
  </fn>
